title: Recognize CC licenses with https URLs
description: https://gpodder.net/directory/+license contains a list of licenses. When selecting a license the podcasts that use this particular license are shown. In https://github.com/gpodder/mygpo/blob/1950aae95d79c87bf703ec7f457fd84c2c9613f4/mygpo/web/utils.py#L204 the license URLs are matched against known patterns to show "nice" names instead of URLs. For creative commons licenses, only http URLs are recognized. http and https URLs should be recognized as identical.

For creative commons licenses, only http URLs are recognized. http and https URLs should be recognized as identical. source-file

title: 500 Error when logging out
description: 500 Error when trying to log out of gpodder.net See sentry Error https://sentry.io/organizations/skoegl/issues/2028765410/?project=1778079 fix: as per https://stackoverflow.com/questions/63394004/client-object-has-no-attribute-deletetouch-in-django-admin-logout-section, we may need to update memecached client.

title: Developer docs insufficient to run test suite
description: Tried to get a dev environment up and running to help out with #233. I followed the [installation instructions](https://gpoddernet.readthedocs.io/en/latest/dev/installation.html) and the [Postgres setup](https://gpoddernet.readthedocs.io/en/latest/dev/postgres-setup.html). I could run the development server fine, but when I ran `make test`, it failed for a couple of different reasons. The development instructions should include all steps necessary to run the tests as well. The steps that are missing: - Create the `envs/tests` directory with appropriate values - Create the `envs/tests/MEDIA_ROOT` file with a value - Create the `envs/dev` directory with appropriate values I got the tests passing by `cp -r envs/local envs/test`, then updating the `envs/test/DATABASE_URL` appropriately, then `mkdir -p media/test && echo media/test > envs/test/MEDIA_ROOT`, then `ln -s local envs/dev`. At this point, the tests ran and passed. I don't know if those steps are correct. I don't know what MEDIA_ROOT is supposed to be -- it's not documented on the [configuration page](https://gpoddernet.readthedocs.io/en/latest/dev/configuration.html). I also don't know what the difference is between `envs/dev` and `envs/local`. Are they just different naming choices for your development environment? If so, the `makefile` is inconsistent, because `dev-config` uses "local" while `test` used "dev". Forgive my noobness -- I don't know Python or Django, so maybe that's some of my problem :slightly_smiling_face: And, as always, thank you for gpodder! Hoping to contribute to help it stay in operation

title: Trying again
description: After several tries and a break I try to install mygpo on my *cubietruck* running *armbian*. I followed all your instructions on http://gpoddernet.readthedocs.io/en/latest/dev/installation.html and got up to `cd mygpo python manage.py migrate` .
